  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Make Kyabondo Livable Village for 3768 People</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support planting 30000 trees in Kyabondo for anti erosive hedges, ditches &amp; wooden dams to prevent devastating erosions. In rainy season, 3768 people victims of natural disasters-landslides, river floods, rolling stones from hills. Houses, house wares, cattle, crops and fertile soil washed away leaving homeless poor families . They begged to be relocated. Authorities said nowhere to resettle them. Since 2014, CADRE supports their initiatives to stabilize the village for safety and prosperity.</narrative>
  </description>
